# Module Boundaries & Dependency Rules

> This document defines what each module may depend on. `scripts/check-architecture.sh`
> enforces the rules listed here; edit both together.

## Allowed dependency direction

```
{{LAYER_ORDER}}
```

Higher-index layers may import from lower-index layers. The reverse is a
violation.

## Forbidden patterns

| From | To | Why | Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| ui/ | repo/ | UI must not touch data access directly | Route through runtime/ or service/ |
| repo/ | service/ | Repo must not depend on business logic | Extract an interface in repo/, implement in service/ |
| any layer | console.log | Use structured logging | Replace with the project logger |

## Exemptions

Document any legitimate cross-layer call here with a reason + a tracking
issue. The architecture check ignores files matching the patterns in its
exemption list (configure in `scripts/check-architecture.sh` if needed).

